  "text": "From the Fig. 3 , it is observed that the asymptotic approximation to the wave number and amplitude are in very good agreement with the direct numerics. Also, the humps in the 'middle' region of DSWs are captured well for both BO and sBO cases. However, it has to be reported that some phase deviations are noticed at the leading edge under enlargement of the figures. This phenomena is explained by Whitham Theory. According to theory, an order epsilon change in the phase θ causes an order one deviation in the location of humps at the leading edge. For the KdV eq., it was predicted in the work [CITATION_1] by using integrable theory. Similar investigation can be performable for BO/sBO equations as a future study.",
